text: I’ve had some tough meetings this week. On very different topics. One is an engineering discussion that I’m not quite managing to convince people that the problem I’ve seen with our code is a big enough problem to fix (it will be expensive to fix), which I’m finding very challenging. The other set of meetings are about my career and what I want to do next. I’m trying to decide between taking a job that needs lots of time talking to customers, and a job that will mean managing an important team.
Nigel is a great speaker, and I hope that you pick the correct route in you career, both sound interesting and very important in their own ways

Thanks! Both will give me a really good opportunity to push Arm to do some awesome things. Did you see Amazon announced Arm instanced are now available in Amazon Web Services - it is really cool to have been part of that happening <https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws/new-ec2-instances-a1-powered-by-arm-based-aws-graviton-processors/>
